  "prompt": "If I got a minor customs infraction when entering Canada, do other countries like China or France know about the customs infraction that I got?",
  "response": "Generally, minor customs infractions are not typically shared between countries and would not likely be accessible to customs officials in other countries such as China or France. Most minor customs issues are resolved within the country where the infraction occurred and do not lead to international records.\n\nHowever, more serious offenses, especially those involving criminal activity or significant fines, might be recorded in international databases or shared during specific international security checks. It is always best to comply with customs regulations in each country to avoid potential complications.",
